<title>USA: Hoechst unit gets FDA ok on prostate assay.</title>
<headline>Hoechst unit gets FDA ok on prostate assay.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-07-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Behring Diagnostics GmbHN, a member of Hoechst Group, said Monday that it has received clearance from the U.S. Food and Drug Admistration to market its OPUS assay for the measurement of prostate specific antigen in serum.</p>
<p>Prostate specific antigen, or PSA, is a secretion of the prostate epithelium and is also produced by prostate cancer cells.</p>
<p>Determining the concentration of PSA in serum can have significant value in detecting metastatic or persistent disease in patients following surgical or medical treatment of prostate cancer.</p>
</text>
